article.headline: High Point 65, Gardner-Webb 51
article.story: HIGH POINT, N.C. (AP) -- Arizona Reid scored 23 points to lift High Point past Gardner-Webb 65-51 on Saturday. Mike Jefferson added 15 points and Troy Bowen had nine for the Panthers (7-4), who took advantage of 21 Gardner-Webb turnovers and three scoreless droughts that lasted more than six minutes each. Takayo Siddle led Gardner-Webb with 13 points but had three turnovers and no assists for the Bulldogs (2-7). Thomas Sanders came off the bench to score seven points and grab seven rebounds for Gardner-Webb, which shot 39.6 percent overall and 24.0 percent from 3-point range.
